
[1]spoon

   SPOON, n.

   1. A small domestic utensil, with a bowl or concave part and a handle,
   for dipping liquids; as a tea spoon; a table spoon.

   2. An instrument consisting of a bowl or hollow iron and a long handle,
   used for taking earth out of holes dug for setting posts.

   SPOON, v.i. To put before the wind in a gale. [I believe not now used.]
